name: Dårlig Hjort
description:
Limited edition (50)
The illustration is a pun on the norwegian expression "dårlig gjort" (doesn't translate very well to English, but means something that is unfair or simply malice). in norwegian, dårlig hjort means bad deer or sick deer).

Its printed with glow-in-the-dark paint on black 200g tees. The print stays crisp no matter where you go :) 

This shirt is currently not available, but we'll be printing new shirts soon.
